    • Method Detail

      • getNnumber

        public long getNnumber()
        Returns:
        Gives number of values stored in the output sequence.

      • getSum

        public double getSum()
        Returns:
        Sample sequence: gives sum of sample values. Trajectory sequence: gives the area below the trajectory function.

      • getMean

        public double getMean()
        Returns:
        Sample sequence: sum/number Trajectory sequence: sum/(tf-t0)

      • getSumSquares

        public double getSumSquares()
        Returns:
        Sample sequence: sum of the square of the samples Trajectory sequence: the area below the square of the trajectory function.

      • getVariance

        public double getVariance()
        Returns:
        meanSquares - mean^2

      • getStdDev

        public double getStdDev()
        Returns:
        Square root of the variance

      • getMeanSquares

        public double getMeanSquares()
        Returns:
        Sample sequence: sumSquares/number Trajectory sequence: sumSquares/(t0-tf)

      • put

        public void put(double tm,
                double val)
        Adding data to sequence (sample or trajectory)
        Parameters:
        tm - For trajectory sequences represents the time when a change in the trajectory function occurs.
        val - For trajectory sequences, represents the new value of the trajectory function; for smaple sequences, represents a new sample value.

      • get

        public void get(double[] tmVal)
         throws java.io.EOFException
        Get a value from the output sequence. For both sample and trajectory sequences. To read from start of for first time, run rewindSet() first. When end of file is reached, method will generate EOFException
        Parameters:
        tmVal - - a array double with two values tmVal[0] - time, tmVal[1] - value.
        Throws:
        java.io.EOFException - End of file exception.

      • computeTrjDSOVs

        public void computeTrjDSOVs(double time0,
                            double timef)
        Method that updates the attributes of the object by treating the recorded values as a trajectory sequence.
        Parameters:
        time0 - Start time of the observation interval, typically 0.
        timef - End time of the observation interval.

      • computePhiDSOVs

        public void computePhiDSOVs()
        Method that updates the attributes of the object by treating the recorded values as a sample sequence.

      • clearSet

        public void clearSet()
        Clears the contents of the output sequence. Can be used to eliminate recorded values after a warm up period.

      • rewindSet

        public boolean rewindSet()
        Rewind Set and open for input.
        Returns:
        - true if rewind was successful, and false otherwise.
